---
name: verify-design-against-code-not-just-architecture
description: "A design contract must be verified against the actual code/substrate, not only by adversarial architecture review — the latter misses exists-vs-build and contradictions with shipped/signed mechanisms"
metadata: 
  node_type: memory
  type: feedback
  originSessionId: 60b48af5-141d-42fb-8d85-51d4010f8eb3
---

The OPP-12 record-lifecycle design ([[opp12-record-lifecycle-protocol]]) passed **4 adversarial
ARCHITECTURE rounds** (Fable 5) + a correctness pass, yet a code-grounded audit found it was **~90%
net-new while reading as near-shipped**, and it **contradicted shipped / HITL-signed mechanisms**:

- currency is the shipped **`superseded_at`** logical_id-alone partial-unique index (G0 / ADR-0.8.0,
  `UNIQUE(logical_id) WHERE superseded_at IS NULL`), NOT an invented `is_latest` column;
- banning "tombstone" / `t_invalid` collides with frozen schema/engine vocab + a live edge column;
- temporal validity is **EDGE-ONLY, ISO-8601 text, inline `datetime('now')`** — not node-level integer
  windows via `SearchFilter` + a bound `:now`;
- the engine **already owns an async projection worker pool** — contradicting the "no-daemon, host-driven,
  sync-inline default" model;
- there is **no EAV / property-FTS** store (only `body`-FTS), so the projection registry has nothing to
  project from.

**Why:** architecture review checks *internal consistency*, not fidelity to the substrate. Consistent /
green ≠ correct-vs-reality — same family as [[conformance-rewrite-vacuous-green-trap]] and
[[release-dod-requires-full-workspace-gate]].

**How to apply:** before drafting/committing a design contract, run a **code-grounded pass** (grep the real
schema/engine) and add an explicit **"what exists today vs net-new"** delta; reconcile every claim's naming
with shipped/signed decisions; mark net-new pieces as net-new. Memex's code-verified response + the HITL
caught this after the fact — do it *before*. Audit saved at `dev/design/record-lifecycle-protocol/code-grounded-audit.md`.

