## Verdict: CONCERN

## Addressed
- Prior finding 1 is resolved. The scorer now routes all of its measurement points through `fts5_tokenize`: query-term extraction, corpus df/avg-field-length pass, and per-candidate tf/field-length counting in [lib.rs](/home/coreyt/projects/fathomdb-worktrees/0.8.14-slice-10-20260704T002826Z/src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/src/lib.rs:10302), [lib.rs](/home/coreyt/projects/fathomdb-worktrees/0.8.14-slice-10-20260704T002826Z/src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/src/lib.rs:10373).
- The temp tokenizer uses the same literal tokenizer as `search_index_v2`: `porter unicode61 remove_diacritics 2` in [lib.rs](/home/coreyt/projects/fathomdb-worktrees/0.8.14-slice-10-20260704T002826Z/src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/src/lib.rs:10305) and [lib.rs](/home/coreyt/projects/fathomdb-worktrees/0.8.14-slice-10-20260704T002826Z/src/rust/crates/fathomdb-schema/src/lib.rs:430).
- The new test is real and load-bearing: [f5_bm25f.rs](/home/coreyt/projects/fathomdb-worktrees/0.8.14-slice-10-20260704T002826Z/src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/tests/f5_bm25f.rs:141) checks `run`→`running` and `cafe`→`café` produce scores `> 0`, which the old lowercase/alnum splitter would have made `0.0`.
- The round-trip itself looks correct in the current design: bound SQL parameter for the text, `DELETE` before reinsert, empty token stream returns `Vec::new()`, and `bm25f_search` holds the engine connection mutex for the whole call in [lib.rs](/home/coreyt/projects/fathomdb-worktrees/0.8.14-slice-10-20260704T002826Z/src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/src/lib.rs:4847), so the temp table is not exposed to overlapping use on the same connection.
- Prior finding 2 is only partially addressed: the runtime write-path comment is fixed in [lib.rs](/home/coreyt/projects/fathomdb-worktrees/0.8.14-slice-10-20260704T002826Z/src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/src/lib.rs:10247).

### 1. [low] Step-17 migration comment still claims `search_index_v2.status` is the G10 status source
Refs: [lib.rs](/home/coreyt/projects/fathomdb-worktrees/0.8.14-slice-10-20260704T002826Z/src/rust/crates/fathomdb-schema/src/lib.rs:413), [lib.rs](/home/coreyt/projects/fathomdb-worktrees/0.8.14-slice-10-20260704T002826Z/src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/src/lib.rs:10247)

The engine-side comment now correctly says F5’s `status` column is its own `$.status`-derived field and not what shipped G10 reads. But the step-17 migration comment in `fathomdb-schema` still says the opposite: “the same status the G10 SearchFilter reads.” That is still inaccurate against the current codepath, where G10 remains wired to vec0’s `status` sentinel semantics. The original low-severity stale-comment finding is therefore not fully resolved.

